The paper proposes a new approach to perform scalable concolic execution, which is a program analysis technique. This technique is related to software engineering (cs.SE), as it aims to improve the efficiency of program analysis. The paper also discusses finding bugs in programs, which is related to computer security (cs.CR). The approach involves program synthesis, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions using a SMT solver, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the approach on real-world applications and a fuzzer test suite, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) as fuzzer test suites are often used in machine learning research.
